        "title": "Google Transliteration API: How to take the input &amp; save the output in a text file?",
        "body": "<p>Greetings All;<\/p>\n\n<p>I need to use google translitrate api in a java application.<\/p>\n\n<p>What I have done till now is to import the sample in the library \"<em>gwt-language-1.1.0<\/em>\" that called \"<em>hellolanguage<\/em>\" in the netbeans, then I added the required libraries/jars.<\/p>\n\n<p>It worked fine like this demo:\n<a href=\"http://gwt.google.com/samples/hellolanguage-1.1.0/HelloLanguage.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">hellolanguage Demo<\/a>\nbut on my localhost.<\/p>\n\n<p>what I want to do is to transliterate data from \"inputfile.txt\" for example and put the output in an \"outputfile.txt\".<\/p>\n\n<p>I don't know how to implement this idea?<\/p>\n\n<p>I'll be glad if you help me.<\/p>\n\n<p>Best regards;<\/p>\n",
