        "creation_date": 1300274953,
        "body": "<p>You'll want to take a look at the Java IO API, for which there is a good tutorial at Oracle. <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/essential/io/charstreams.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">This part<\/a> of the tutorial will be particularly useful, and should provide some cut-and-pasteable code.<\/p>\n\n<p>You can find a good Google Transliteration API example <a href=\"http://www.google.com/codesearch/p?hl=en#ow6Lmd7dcZY/trunk/language/language/test/com/google/gwt/language/client/transliteration/text/TransliterationTest.java&amp;q=com.google.gwt.language.client.transliteration.text.Transliteration&amp;d=8\" rel=\"nofollow\">here<\/a>. You'll want to add your custom code in the part of the code that looks like this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>new TransliterationCallback() {\n\n@Override\nprotected void onCallback(TransliterationResult result) {\n// your code here\n}\n\n});\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
